Package org.eng.aisp.dataset

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IDoubleDataSet<WINDOW extends ILabeledDataWindow<double[]>>
    Holds a set of double data window references with associated labeling and tagging.
    ILabeledDataSet<DATA,WINDOW extends ILabeledDataWindow<DATA>>
    Extends the IShuffleIterable over ILabeledDataWindows to enable extraction of the labeling information.
    IReferencedDataSpec<DATA extends ILabeledDataWindow<?>>
    Represents a reference to data that will be assigned the labels and tags contained in this implementation instance.
    IReferencedSoundSpec
    Extends the super class to add optional segmenting of the referenced sound.
    ISoundDataSet
    Holds a set of sound references with associated labeling, tagging and other data.
    ISoundReferenceSet
    Holds a set of sound references with associated labeling and tagging.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractSoundReferenceSet
    Holds labeling, tags and other metadata on a set of reference sounds.
    ComposedSoundDataSet
    Extends the super class to compose SoundRecordings using the apply() method of a referencing IReferencedSoundSpec.
    ComposedStoredSoundDataSet
    Extends the super class to use IReferencedSoundSpecStorage and ISoundStorage as the IReferencedSoundSpec and SoundRecording dereferencers needed by the super class.
    LabeledSoundFiles
    Helper class to manage sounds and associated metadata files.
    MetaData
    Represents a CSV file of labels and tags to be applied to named sound files.
    MetaData.Record
    A simple extension of SoundReference that currently does not allow segmenting of the reference clip.
    MetaDataZip
    Provides a way to write one or more sounds with and metadata file into a ZIP stream.
    MetaDataZip.NamedSound
    Holds the name (typically a file name from a zip file) associated with the sound.
    ReferencedSoundSpec
    A simple/obvious implementation of IReferencedSoundSpec.
